 Myr and distances (with typical\n$1\\sigma$-uncertainties of about 10-15%) from 30 to 100 kpc. Except for one\nobject (B711), which we reclassify as A-type star, all stars are of spectral\ntype B. The spectroscopic distances and stellar ages derived here are key\ningredients for upcoming kinematic studies of HVSs based on Gaia proper\nmotions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 22 Jun 2018 12:37:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-18"}
